# bronze-pipeline-definition.json

This pipeline definition orchestrates the Bronze ingestion process for the Lakehouse. It references the ingestion script, schema, and configuration files to ensure deterministic, repeatable processing of raw data into the Bronze layer.

The pipeline is modular and environmentâ€‘agnostic, making it suitable for execution within any orchestration framework, including Databricks Jobs, Fabric Pipelines, Airflow, or other enterprise schedulers. All paths, parameters, and retry behaviors are explicitly defined to support reliable automation and operational transparency.

{
  "pipeline_name": "bronze_ingestion_pipeline",
  "description": "Ingest raw sales data into the Bronze layer using deterministic schema and configuration.",
  "tasks": [
    {
      "name": "bronze_ingestion",
      "type": "spark_python",
      "script_path": "scripts/bronze/bronze-ingestion.py",
      "config_path": "configs/bronze/bronze-ingestion-config.json",
      "schema_path": "configs/bronze/bronze-schema.json",
      "retry": {
        "max_attempts": 3,
        "delay_seconds": 60
      }
    }
  ],
  "schedule": {
    "type": "manual",
    "enabled": true
  },
  "notifications": {
    "on_success": "log_only",
    "on_failure": "alert"
  }
}